ry\n the hash value the path of the duplicate duplicate\n this image\n            else:\n # If this and hash value do\'t match, add is not a duplicate\n                hashes[img_hash] = size # Add the value size to to this image\n    return duplicates\n\n Return dictionary of duplicate images\n\ndef remove_duplicates(duplicates):\n    """Remove duplicate images"""\n    for img1, img2 in duplicates.items(): # Iterate over dictionary of duplicate\n        for i in img2:            os.remove(i) # Remove duplicate image\n```\n\nI this helps! Let me know if you have any other questions.user\n\nI you please provide a error on a to the user to follow the path path and \n\n would be really to have a user-friendly interface'
